cedonia ohio other occupation engineer rank major general usaf time in space d h m selection  nasa group missions sts sts mission insignia ronald ron michael sega also ronald šega phd born december   is professor of systems engineering and vice president for energy and the environment at the colorado state university research foundation a nonprofit advocacy organization supporting csu he is also the vice president and enterprise executive for energy and environment at the ohio state university from august  to august  he served as under secretary of the air force he is a retired major general in the united states air force and a former nasa astronaut sega was born in cleveland ohio he is of slovene origin he was married to fellow astronaut bonnie j dunbar he is now married to ann sega and they have two sons contents  education  career  nasa career  space flight experience  postnasa career  awards and honors  organizations  references  external links educationedit sega graduated from nordonia high school macedonia ohio in  after which he received a bachelor of science degree in mathematics and physics from the united states air force academy in  a master of science degree in physics from ohio state university in  and a doctorate in electrical engineering from university of colorado at boulder in  careeredit this section of a biography of a living person does not include any references or sources please help by adding reliable sources contentious material about living people that is unsourced or poorly sourced must be removed immediately find sources ronald m sega – news · newspapers · books · scholar · jstor september  learn how and when to remove this template message sega completed pilot training in  and served as an instructor pilot at williams air force base arizona until  from  to  he was on the faculty of the united states air force academy in the physics department where he designed and constructed a laboratory facility to investigate microwave fields using infrared techniques while pursuing a doctorate in electrical engineering in  he joined the faculty of the university of colorado at colorado springs as assistant professor in the department of electrical and computer engineering he was promoted to associate professor in  granted tenure in  promoted to professor in  and is currently on an extended leave of absence from  to  he served as technical director lasers and aerospace mechanics directorate of the frank j seiler research laboratory at the us air force academy from  to  while on leave from the university of colorado he served as research associate professor of physics at the university of houston affiliated with the space vacuum epitaxy center and is adjunct professor of physics sega is a coprincipal investigator and mission director for the wake shield facility wsf which has flown on space shuttle mission sts in february  and sts in  he has authored or coauthored over  technical publications as a pilot sega has logged over  hours in the air force air force reserves and nasa nasa careeredit sega became an astronaut in july  after selection in  his technical assignments included working remote manipulator system rms issues for the astronaut office mission development branch supporting orbiter software verification in the shuttle avionics integration laboratory sail chief of astronaut appearances science support group lead space station integration team astronaut representative to the space station science and utilization advisory board primarily an external board for nasa from november  to march  sega was the nasa director of operations star city russia the gagarin cosmonaut training center responsible for managing nasa activities at star city these activities involved building an organization and infrastructure to support astronaut and cosmonaut mission and science training for flight on the russian space station mir he also participated in training on russian space systems and was the first american to train in the russian eva suit orlan in their underwater facility hydrolaboratory a veteran of two space flights sts in  and sts in  sega logged over  hours in space space flight experienceedit sega was the flight engineer of sts during which the wake shield facility was deployed sts was the first joint united statesrussian space shuttle mission launched on february   sts was the second flight of the space habitation module spacehab and the first flight of the wake shield facility wsf during the day flight the crew of discovery conducted a wide variety of biological materials science earth observation and life science experiments sega was the flight engineer for ascent and entry on this mission performed several experiments on orbit and operated the robotic arm berthing the wake shield onto its payload bay carrier on four separate occasions following  orbits of the earth in  miles sts landed at kennedy space center florida on february   with the completion of his first space flight sega logged  days  hours  minutes in space sega top right with the crew of sts aboard the mir sts the third docking mission to the russian space station mir launched at night on march   with a crew of six aboard atlantis following rendezvous and docking with mir a nasa astronaut transferred to mir for a fivemonth stay to begin a continuous presence of us astronauts aboard mir for the next two years sega was the payload commander for this mission and lead on biorack a small multipurpose laboratory located in the spacehab module carried in the shuttle payload bay biorack was used to technology development fundamental biology research into plant and animal cellular function and environment characterization he was responsible for planning and onorbit operations including extensive transfer of logistics and science including  pounds of science and mission hardware food water and air to mir and returning over  pounds of us and esa science and russian hardware following  orbits of the earth atlantis landed with a crew of five at edwards air force base in california on march   mission duration was  days  hours  minutes postnasa careeredit sega left nasa on july   to become dean of the college of engineering and applied science university of colorado at colorado springs in  he became acting assistant to the secretary of defense for nuclear chemical and biological programs sega served as assistant secretary of defense for research and engineering from august  through august  the defense research and engineering was made by paul wolfowitz the key compliance officer regarding among others the protection of human subjects in dod supported research in the same period he also served as the reserve assistant to the chairman joint chiefs of staff jcs according to the senate armed services committee report of the inquiry into the treatment of detainees in us custody the joint chiefs were involved in the approval of the controversial interrogation program both the dod and the cia engaged in january  during segas tenure as director a dodwide review of human subjects protection policies was initiated by defense research and engineering ddre on november   a navy presentation at a dod training day said the review found the navy not in full compliance with federal policies on human subjects protection it was pointed out that the navy had no single point of accountability for human subject protections in  he became under secretary of the air force thus serving as department of defense executive agent and milestone decision authority for space starting in  he worked at the colorado state university where sega has served as vice president of energy and the environment for the colorado state university research foundation a private nonprofit advocacy organization for the university and as the woodward professor of systems engineering in the college of engineering in september  colorado state university and the ohio state university collaborated to create a shared position called the vice president and enterprise executive for energy and the environment in this position sega will help the institutions work together to identify and lead potential national initiatives and economic development opportunities and will also look for opportunities for collaboration between the universities awards and honorsedit distinguished graduate of the united states air force academy  top graduate of the pilot instructor training course  officer of the year in the department of physics us air force academy  meritorious service medal commendation medal usaf reserve achievement medal air force research fellow — air force office of scientific research  received the outstanding faculty award — department of electrical engineering at the university of colorado  selected to the academic hall of fame of his high school in macedonia ohio  reserve officer of the year ima air force space command  reserve officer of the year ima us air force  received an honorary doctorate from clarkson university  nasa space flight medals  and  nasa superior achievement award  nasa director of operations russia  nasa outstanding leadership medal  colorado space hall of fame on  october  organizationsedit american institute of aeronautics and astronautics aiaa — associate fellow  institute of electrical and electronics engineers ieee american physical society aps institute for the advancement of engineering — fellow  society for photooptical instrumentation engineers spie air force reserve officer association association of space explorers eta kappa nu referencesedit  csu news release august      for new station commander spaceflight is all in the family retrieved    carl levin  april  senate armed services committee releases the report of the inquiry into the treatment of detainees in us custody carl levin us senator michigan retrieved  june    a b jeffrey kaye  october   dod directive changed rules to allow experiments on detainees truthout investigative report retrieved  june    jason leopold jeffrey kaye  october  wolfowitz directive gave legal cover to detainee experimentation program truthout investigative report retrieved  june    biography of ron sega ohio state university news room retrieved    hoffman shelly the ohio state university colorado state university create shared leadership position the ohio state university news room retrieved    brevard business news foundation names honoree for colorado space hall of fame event set for oct  vol  no  melbourne florida  august  p  external linksedit united states air force portal nasa biography government offices preceded by hans m mark director of defense research and engineering – succeeded by john j young jr preceded by peter b teets united states under secretary of the air force  –  succeeded by vacant  erin c conaton v t e nasa astronaut group  the hairballs  nasa astronaut group  ← nasa astronaut group  → nasa astronaut group  pilots kenneth cockrell eileen collins william g gregory james d halsell charles j precourt richard a searfoss terrence w wilcutt mission specialists daniel w bursch leroy chiao michael r clifford nancy j currie bernard a harris jr susan helms thomas d jones william s mcarthur james h newman ellen ochoa ronald m sega donald a thomas janice e voss carl e walz peter wisoff david wolf v t e nasa astronaut groups nasa astronaut corps                       list of astronauts by year of selection authority control worldcat identities viaf  lccn n retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitleronaldmsegaoldid categories  birthsliving peopleamerican astronautsamerican engineersohio state university alumnimilitary personnel from clevelandamerican people of slovenian descentunited states air force academy alumniunited states air force officersuniversity of colorado alumniuniversity of colorado facultyuniversity of houston facultygeorge w bush administration personnelamerican astronautpoliticiansunited states assistant secretaries of defensehidden categories blp articles lacking sou