uman subjects protection it was pointed out that the navy had no single point of accountability for human subject protections in  he became under secretary of the air force thus serving as department of defense executive agent and milestone decision authority for space starting in  he worked at the colorado state university where sega has served as vice president of energy and the environment for the colorado state university research foundation a private nonprofit advocacy organization for the university and as the woodward professor of systems engineering in the college of engineering in september  colorado state university and the ohio state university collaborated to create a shared position called the vice president and enterprise executive for energy and the environment in this position sega will help the institutions work together to identify and lead potential national initiatives and economic development opportunities and will also look for opportunities for collaboration between the universities awards and honorsedit distinguished graduate of the united states air force academy  top graduate of the pilot instructor training course  officer of the year in the department of physics us air force academy  meritorious service medal commendation medal usaf reserve achievement medal air force research fellow — air force office of scientific research  received the outstanding faculty award — department of electrical engineering at the university of colorado  selected to the academic hall of fame of his high school in macedonia ohio  reserve officer of the year ima air force space command  reserve officer of the year ima us air force  received an honorary doctorate from clarkson university  nasa space flight medals  and  nasa superior achievement award  nasa director of operations russia  nasa outstanding leadership medal  colorado space hall of fame on  october  organizationsedit american institute of aeronautics and astronautics aiaa — associate fellow  institute of electrical and electronics engineers ieee american physical society aps institute for the advancement of engineering — fellow  society for photooptical instrumentation engineers spie air force reserve officer association association of space explorers eta kappa nu referencesedit  csu news release august      for new station commander spaceflight is all in the family retrieved    carl levin  april  senate armed services committee releases the report of the inquiry into the treatment of detainees in us custody carl levin us senator michigan retrieved  june    a b jeffrey kaye  october   dod directive changed rules to allow experiments on detainees truthout investigative report retrieved  june    jason leopold jeffrey kaye  october  wolfowitz directive gave legal cover to detainee experimentation program truthout investigative report retrieved  june    biography of ron sega ohio state university news room retrieved    hoffman shelly the ohio state university colorado state university create shared leadership position the ohio state university news room retrieved    brevard business news foundation names honoree for colorado space hall of fame event set for oct  vol  no  melbourne florida  august  p  external linksedit united states air force portal nasa biography government offices preceded by hans m mark director of defense research and engineering – succeeded by john j young jr preceded by peter b teets united states under secretary of the air force  –  succeeded by vacant  erin c conaton v t e nasa astronaut group  the hairballs  nasa astronaut group  ← nasa astronaut group  → nasa astronaut group  pilots kenneth cockrell eileen collins william g gregory james d halsell charles j precourt richard a searfoss terrence w wilcutt mission specialists daniel w bursch leroy chiao michael r clifford nancy j currie bernard a harris jr susan helms thomas d jones william s mcarthur james h newman ellen ochoa ronald m sega donald a thomas janice e voss carl e walz peter wis