eenvironmental health  safetyeu informationnewsroomplants  officesprincipal lines of businessproducts and servicessocial responsibilitysupplier diversitysix sigma dr ronald m sega  vice president and enterprise executive for energy and the environment colorado state university and the ohio state university dr ronald m sega is vice president and enterprise executive for energy and the environment with colorado state university and the ohio state university he was elected director of woodward in  sega also serves on the board of directors for rentech inc dr sega served as under secretary for the us air force and flew as a nasa astronaut on two shuttle missions as under secretary dr sega lead a team that developed a comprehensive energy strategy emphasizing supply demand and culture he has authored or coauthored more than  technical publications and has served on numerous advisory and governance boards dr sega graduated from the air force academy received a master’s degree from the ohio state university and earned a doctorate in electrical engineering from the university of colorado he retired from the us air force in the rank of major general              suppliersapplying to be a woodward suppliersupplier faqsupplier gateway communitycommunity events contact usterms and conditionsglossary copyright  woodward inc